article.headline: Utah St. 77, Prairie View 51
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll scored 19 points to lead Utah State past Prairie View A&M 77-51 Saturday night. Stephen DuCharme added 12 for Utah State (7-5) and Tai Wesley added 11. Aaron Smith was the high scorer for the Panthers (2-7) with 12 points. The Aggies led by as many as 30 points and played their bench for much of the second half. The closest Prairie View could get was 17 points early in the second half until the Aggies extended their lead. USU had 14 steals and the Panthers were assessed 23 turnovers.
